<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-23 00:54 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wizards 1, Mutiny 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Mo Johnston scored in the sixth minute
as the Kansas City Wizards shut out Tampa Bay 1-0 Saturday night to
improve Major League Soccer's best record to 5-0-1.
</P>
<P>
   Johnston put Kansas City (5-0-1) ahead after taking a restart
from Matt McKeon, who lofted a long pass over the Mutiny defense.
Johnston went across the box and fired the ball past goalie Scott
Garlick and into the far corner of the net.
</P>
<P>
   Wizards goalie Tony Meola registered his league-best fourth
shutout.
</P>
<P>
   The Mutiny (3-3-0) are scoreless in 270 minutes of away play,
the longest road scoreless streak in team history.
</P>
<P>
   Kalin Bankov had Tampa Bay's only shot on goal in the first
half.
</P>
<P>
   Trying to spark his team's offense, Mutiny coach Tim Hankinson
benched Raul Diaz Arce and Dominic Kinnear in favor of Manny Lagos
and Eric Quill in the second half.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-04-23-00 0054 </TRAILER>
