</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Little Havana Protesters Arrested
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   MIAMI (AP) -- Riot police with batons and shields beat down rioting
demonstrators on the streets of Little Havana on Saturday after Elian Gonzalez
was snatched away by federal agents. More than 260 people were arrested.
Protests and sporadic violence began minutes after the pre-dawn raid on Lazaro
Gonzalez's house and spread across the neighborhood, with demonstrators starting
hundreds of small fires and uprooting concrete benches into the street. As the
night wore on and police closed streets and clamped down on protesters, parades
of honking cars poured into surrounding neighborhoods.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Miami Kin Try To See Elian, Dad
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Miami relatives of Elian Gonzalez followed him to
