<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-23 01:24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Earthquakes 5, Burn 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) -- Ronald Cerritos and Abdul Thompson
Conteh scored two goals apiece Saturday night as the San Jose
Earthquakes broke out of a scoring slump with a 5-0 victory over
the Dallas Burn.
</P>
<P>
   The Earthquakes (2-2-1), who entered the game with a league-low
three goals, went ahead after just 10 minutes, when Cerritos
crossed a ball into the middle for Conteh, who was knocked down in
the box. Cerritos converted the resulting penalty kick.
</P>
<P>
   Four minutes later, Burn goalie Matt Jordan, pressured by
Cerritos, slipped and fell as he attempted to clear the ball. Dario
Brose collected the ball and fired it in before Jordan could
recover.
</P>
<P>
   The Sharks tallied twice in four minutes again before halftime,
with Cerritos making it 3-0 in the 36th minute and Conteh adding
another in the 40th.
</P>
<P>
   Conteh closed the scoring with 20 minutes remaining. Ian Russell
took the ball on the left side of the box, then crossed to the
right post. The ball went over a Dallas defender's head to Conteh,
who drove a shot past Jordan.
</P>
<P>
   Dallas fell to 3-3.
</P>
</TEXT>
