95-85 in their playoff opener. Game 2 in the best-of-five series is Tuesday.
Alonzo Mourning blocked nine shots, a Heat playoff record, spearheading a strong
defensive effort. The Pistons committed 18 turnovers and finished 18 points
below their regular-season average of 103.5 per game, second-best in the NBA.
Mashburn's point total was a career playoff high.
