<HEADLINE> Singapore Price Index Falls  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SINGAPORE (AP) -- Singapore's consumer price index for March was
down 0.3 percent over February, reflecting cheaper food and lower
transportation and communication costs, the Department of
Statistics said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   The CPI was 1.2 percent higher than in March of last year.
</P>
<P>
   Food prices fell by 1.6 percent in March 2000, due mainly to
cheaper seafood, vegetables and fresh pork, the department said in
a statement.
</P>
<P>
   The price of clothing went up 1.4 percent, while housing and
health care costs were unchanged.
</P>
</TEXT>
