<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-23 15:23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Def Jam Founder Adds Retail Store  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Def Jam Records co-founder Russell Simmons is
adding a retail store to his growing list of ventures outside the
music arena.
</P>
<P>
   The planned 14,000-square-foot flagship store in Harlem will
carry Simmons' own Phat Farm clothing line, as well as that of
hip-hop mogul Sean ''Puff Daddy'' Combs, Polo and Versace.
</P>
<P>
   But it also will offer items ranging from home furnishings and
jewelry to pagers, he said.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's a megastore. It's a lifestyle store,'' Simmons told the
New York Post. And it is ''the first of what should be many, many
stores.''
</P>
<P>
   The rap music impresario said he is in the final stages of
lining up a lease for the property.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
