<HEADLINE> Six Killed in Kentucky Car Crash  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WINCHESTER, Ky. (AP) -- A van crossed the center line of the
Mountain Parkway in eastern Kentucky and struck another vehicle
nearly head-on, killing six people and injuring three others, State
Police said.
</P>
<P>
   The cause of the wreck was still under investigation Sunday but
officers said alcohol was not believed to have been a factor.
</P>
<P>
   The driver of the van lost control Saturday evening about nine
miles east of Winchester, and the vehicle swerved into the opposite
lane, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The accident happened in clear weather in an area before the
highway enters mountainous sections of eastern Kentucky.
</P>
<P>
   State police identified the victims as Emanuel Miller, 21;
Catherene Burke, 19; Jimmy Miller, 13, and App Miller, 14, all of
Jackson all in the van; and Ricky J. Lucas, 37, and Don W. Ratliff,
62.
</P>
<P>
   Police said Emanuel Miller was driving the van and was the only
one wearing a seat belt. Police could not say for sure Sunday how
any of the victims were related.
</P>
</TEXT>
