<HEADLINE> Colombian Rebels Kidnap 12  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) -- At least 12 people were kidnapped by a
leftist rebel faction when a landslide blocked holiday traffic on a
rural highway, officials said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Guerrillas from the People's Liberation Army, or EPL, snatched
their victims from buses and private cars near the town of
Riosucio, 130 miles northeast of Bogota, said Highway Police
commander Col. Alvaro Sandoval.
</P>
<P>
   Leftist rebels often mount roadblocks on isolated country roads,
especially on holiday weekends, charging ransoms for the release of
their victims.
</P>
<P>
   The 500-strong EPL is the smallest of Colombia's main guerrilla
groups.
</P>
