<HEADLINE> Palestinian Activist Office Closed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   JERUSALEM (AP) -- The Palestinian Authority shut down the Gaza
City office of a Palestinian political activist group, the
organization said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Members of the Civic Forum Institute said in a statement
released to the press that their office was shut down last week in
a ''blatant violation of basic democratic rights'' by Palestinian
security officials.
</P>
<P>
   The Palestinian police in the Gaza Strip say the office was
closed because it is not registered with the Palestinian Ministry
of the Interior.
</P>
<P>
   The forum, which organizes lectures on refugee and social
issues, is run by Khatem Abdel Khader, a Palestinian legislator,
who has criticized corruption in the Palestinian Authority, but
supports Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat.
</P>
<P>
   Palestinian human rights groups have said that that torture,
political detention and restrictions on speech are rampant under
the Palestinian Authority.
