<HEADLINE> 7.7 Tons of Marijuana Seized  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MEXICO CITY (AP) -- Federal police found 7.7 tons of marijuana
earlier this week when they searched a truck heading to Mexico's
northern border with a load of 246 natural gas tanks, officials
said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   The plastic-wrapped marijuana bundles were found inside the
tanks, after police stopped the truck at a roadside checkpoint
about 90 miles south of the New Mexico border, a statement from the
Attorney General's Office said.
</P>
<P>
   Shortly before, police at the same checkpoint had stopped
another truck and found 46 pounds of cocaine hidden in a secret
compartment aboard the vehicle. The drivers of both trucks were
turned over to magistrates on suspicion of drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
   In another operation on the Pan-American highway, just south of
the border, federal police found a man carrying 7.26 pounds of
heroin in a suitcase aboard a passenger bus. That man was also
detained.
</P>
