<HEADLINE> Expos 6, Brewers 4  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MONTREAL (AP) -- Vladimir Guerrero went 2-for-3 with two RBIs and
was walked intentionally with first base occupied during Montreal's
four-run fourth as the Expos beat the Milwaukee Brewers 6-4 on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Javier Vazquez (2-0) pitched seven innings allowing four hits,
including a three-run homer to Geoff Jenkins, who homered for the
third straight game.
</P>
<P>
   Guerrero hit an RBI single in the first and added his 100th
career double in the third for his 25th RBI of the season. He
raised his average to .439 (29-for-66).
</P>
<P>
   Guerrero was walked intentionally with runners on first and
third and two outs in the fourth after Rondell White singled in the
go-ahead run off Jaime Navarro (0-4) to make it 4-3.
</P>
<P>
   Left-hander Matt Williams replaced Navarro and issued
back-to-back walks to Lee Stevens and Trace Coquillette to increase
Montreal's lead to 6-3.
</P>
<P>
   Ugueth Urbina came on with runners at first and third and two
outs in the eighth and allowed an RBI single to Kevin Barker.
Urbina struck out the final four batters for his fifth save in
seven opportunities.
</P>
<P>
   Leading 2-0 on Guerrero's two RBI hits, Vazquez gave up a
leadoff double to Mark Loretta in the fourth for the Brewers first
hit.
</P>
<P>
   Jeromy Burnitz, who had walked in the first, was hit by a pitch
and Jenkins put Milwaukee ahead 3-2 as he launched a high drive
into the right-field stands for his seventh homer of the season.
</P>
<P>
   The lead was short-lived as the Expos rallied for four in the
bottom half.
</P>
<P>
   Navarro allowed six runs and eight hits in 3 2-3 innings to see
his ERA go from 10.66 to 11.57. He walked four, including two
intentional walks.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Montreal has won six of its last eight home games to raise
its overall record to 10-8. ... Navarro has allowed 28 hits and 15
walks in his four starts. ... The Brewers are 1-4 on their current
nine-game road trip, Milwaukee's second-longest trip of the season.
... Guerrero has 99 career homers. ... Tony Armas threw 80 pitches
Saturday night in a rehab outing for Class-A Jupiter. Armas, who
allowed three runs -- two earned -- and just one hit in 4 1-3
innings, is on the 15-day disabled list with tendinitis in his
right elbow. ... Vazquez has gone at least six innings in each of
his four starts.
</P>
</TEXT>
