<HEADLINE> Quotes From the Elian Gonzalez Case  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Quotes from the Elian Gonzalez case:
<TEXT>
<P>
   ''We waited four, five months, the attorney general herself went
down and tried to negotiate a deal. I'm not sure what much more the
federal government could have been expected to do. We were forced
into the action that we took by the intransigence of that family in
Miami.'' -- Deputy Attorney General Eric Holder.
</P>
<P>
   ''His father speaks for him. He is with his father.'' --
Immigration and Naturalization Service commissioner Doris M.
Meissner.
</P>
<P>
   ''You bet there'll be congressional hearings.'' -- Republican
Whip Tom DeLay of Texas.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's time for some peace here for this boy. It's time for him
to have a chance in solitude and privacy to reconnect with his
family. That's going on right now. And the worst thing that could
possibly happen would be to reintroduce the circus atmosphere, the
television lights, the cameras, and the emotions of Miami into this
family reunion which is so special.'' -- Gregory Craig, attorney for
Juan Miguel Gonzalez.
</P>
<P>
   ''There is absolutely no justification for using force to take a
little boy away from a home in Miami at gunpoint. That's just not
America. I am so disheartened at what I have seen over these last
several days.'' -- Sen. Connie Mack, R-Fla.
</P>
<P>
   ''Today our focus is: examination of any legal options we may
have to make sure that in the coming days no more harm happens to
him.'' -- Kendall Coffey, attorney for the Miami relatives.
</P>
<P>
   ''It seemed to the point that they (the Miami relatives) were
negotiating on a card they did not have. Elian became a Cold War
trophy. The issue really is about Castro.'' Rev. Jesse Jackson,
civil rights leader.
</P>
<P>
   ''I think Juan Miguel was very sensitive. He's not trying to ask
his son questions about what happened yesterday or what's going to
happen tomorrow.'' -- Joan Brown Campbell of the National Council of
Churches and a friend of Juan Miguel Gonzalez who was present at
their reunion.
</P>
<P>
   ''What happened yesterday morning was an armed assault on an
innocent family, an unarmed family, where a young boy was taken
from his home forcefully. ... Their boy was taken from them.'' --
Sen. Bob Smith, R-N.H.
</P>
<P>
   ''Listen, let's get on with it. The cycle is complete. The boy
was snatched from his father five months ago, he was found in the
Atlantic Ocean, he's in this country, he's been here five months,
albeit illegal, he's now this wonderful kid in the loving arms of
his father.'' -- Rep. Charles Rangel, D-N.Y.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
