<HEADLINE> Twins 5, Rangers 4  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARLINGTON, Texas (AP) -- Brad Radke pitched eight strong innings
as the Minnesota Twins beat the Texas Rangers 5-4 on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Radke (2-2) got 18 outs on ground balls to help the Twins to
their second victory in the three-game series. Radke allowed three
runs and nine hits in eight-plus innings.
</P>
<P>
   Radke cruised through he first eight innings before allowing a
double to David Segui and walking Ruben Mateo to start the ninth.
</P>
<P>
   Bob Wells relieved and got two outs before Royce Clayton hit a
three-run homer to right-center field, his third of the season.
</P>
<P>
   After Luis Alicea doubled, Wells got Jason McDonald to ground
out to second for the reliever's third save.
</P>
<P>
   In his previous start, Radke allowed one run and six hits over
eight innings, retiring 24 of the 31 batters he faced in a 3-1
victory over Kansas City.
</P>
<P>
   Texas had beaten Minnesota 13 straight times before the weekend
series. The Twins have won five of six overall.
</P>
<P>
   Ivan Rodriguez's eight-inning RBI single ended Radke's bid for
his fourth career shutout.
</P>
<P>
   Texas has lost six of its last seven.
</P>
<P>
   Minnesota's Matt Lawton drove in two runs and went 3-for-4 to
extend his hitting streak to 10 games, matching his career high.
</P>
<P>
   The Twins scored three runs in the fifth against Darren Oliver
(0-1). Cristian Guzman had an RBI single and Lawton had a two-run
single.
</P>
<P>
   Butch Huskey's sacrifice fly in the eighth pushed Minnesota's
lead to 4-0.
</P>
<P>
   Oliver allowed four runs and nine hits in 7 1-3 innings. He
struck out two and walked three.
</P>
<P>
   Denny Hocking's RBI double in the ninth made it 5-1.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Texas third baseman Mike Lamb singled in the third in his
first major league at-bat. Lamb also committed his first error,
throwing high to first on a sixth-inning grounder. ... Lawton has
hit in 10 straight games three times in his career. ... Texas'
Rafael Palmeiro had a rare triple in the fourth. Palmiero has one
triple in each of the last three seasons. ... The Twins hit into
four double plays. ...Minnesota's Jason Maxwell had his first
three-hit game, going 3-for-4.
</P>
