<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-23 19:43 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Honduras 2, Canada 0  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   HERSHEY, Pa. (AP) -- Hesler Phillips and Luis Ramirez each scored
as Honduras posted a 2-0 victory over Canada in an Olympic soccer
qualifying game Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   With the victory, Honduras (1-1) kept alive its hopes of
advancing to the semifinal round of the six-team tournament, which
will send its top two finishers to the Sydney Games.
</P>
<P>
   Canada (0-1), making its first appearance in the preliminary
round, will play the United States on Tuesday night. The Americans
blanked Honduras 3-0 on Friday and are in excellent shape for
advancing to the final four. The Canadians must defeat the U.S.
team 2-0 or score at least three goals in a victory over the
Americans to move into Friday night's semifinal round.
</P>
<P>
   Otherwise, the Americans and Hondurans move on.
</P>
<P>
   Phillips gave Honduras a 1-0 lead in the 32nd minute when his
shot from about 10 yards flicked off a Canadian defender and soared
over goalkeeper Mike Franks.
</P>
<P>
   Canadian left fullback Jason Mathot was sent off for hitting
Honduras' Elvis Danilo Turcios in the face with about 15 minutes
remaining. Still, Canada had a great chance to tie the game in the
90th minute. But Kevin McKenna's header off Jim Brennan's free kick
smacked the underside of the crossbar, dropped to the goal line and
bounced away.
</P>
<P>
   Moments later, in stoppage time, Ramirez tacked on a goal to
seal it for Honduras.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
