<HEADLINE> Guatemala 1, Mexico 1  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   HERSHEY, Pa. (AP) -- Freddy Garcia's goal in the 80th minute gave
Guatemala a 1-1 tie with favored Mexico on Sunday, advancing the
Guatemalans in the CONCACAF Olympic soccer qualifying tournament.
</P>
<P>
   Guatemala (1-0-1) will play in Friday night's semifinals against
an opponent to be determined. Mexico (0-0-1) and Panama (0-1) will
play Tuesday night to determine the other team from the three-team
group to advance.
</P>
<P>
   Honduras defeated Canada 2-0 in the first game of the
double-header. The United States, which defeated Honduras 3-0 on
Friday night, will play Canada on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   With his team trailing 1-0, Garcia uncorked a shot toward the
left post off a header from teammate Dwight Pezzalossi. Airborne
Mexican keeper Adrian Zermeno was unable to catch the ball, opting
to smack it into the air. Zermeno then tumbled into the cage and
the ball landed on top of him for the tying goal.
</P>
<P>
   Mexico took the lead late in the 43rd minute when a blistering
strike by Hector Altamirano from just off the left touchline was
headed in by Joaquin Beltran. Guatemala keeper Luis Pedro Molina
had a chance at Beltran's redirected shot, but the ball went
through his outstretched hands and landed in the right corner of
the net.
</P>
</TEXT>
