<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-23 21:23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Caffe Latte Wins At Santa Barbara  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARCADIA, Calif. (AP) -- In a duel between two of the country's
top turf females, Caffe Latte overtook Happyanunoit entering the
stretch to win the Santa Anita Park's $250,000 Santa Barbara
Handicap on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Caffe Latte beat Happyanunoit by three-quarters of a length and
finished in 2:00 2/5.
</P>
<P>
   ''This is a very special filly,'' Corey Nakatani said after what
was his fourth of six riding victories on the card.
</P>
<P>
   Happyanunoit, the 19-10 favorite who hadn't raced since
November, dug in determinedly with Brice Blanc while finishing four
lengths ahead of Country Garden in third.
</P>
<P>
   Spanish Fern, Aistoire Sainte and Marie de Bayeux completed the
order of finish.
</P>
<P>
   Caffe Latte, the 2-1 second choice who carried 116 pounds, paid
$6.40, $3 and $2.60. Happyanunoit, the 121-pound high weight, paid
$3.20 and $2.60. Country Garden, ridden by Eddie Delahoussaye, paid
$4 to show.
</P>
<P>
   By winning six races with eight mounts during the 10-race
program, Nakatani became the eighth jockey in Santa Anita Park's
63-year history to win six races on a single card. The last was
Martin Pedroza in 1992.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
