<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-23 23:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rockies Accuse Cardinals Catcher  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ST. LOUIS (AP) -- The Colorado Rockies believe St. Louis' Eli
Marrero tried to get hit by a pitch Sunday in the Cardinals' 6-3
rain-shortened victory.
</P>
<P>
   Pitcher Scott Karl accused Marrero of leaning his elbow into a
pitch in the second inning, loading the bases. One batter later,
Placido Polanco hit a grand slam to cap a five-run inning.
</P>
<P>
   Karl said the pitch was a strike, and that Marrero leaned over
the plate. He and manager Buddy Bell complained about the situation
for several minutes with home plate umpire Angel Hernandez.
</P>
<P>
   ''If he wants to get hit so badly, I'm sure somebody else out
there will accommodate him,'' Karl said. ''As long as major league
baseball lets people stand up there guarded like tanks, what can
you do about it?''
</P>
<P>
   Replays appeared to confirm that Marrero stuck out his elbow.
</P>
<P>
   ''He leaned right into the pitch because he's got an elbow pad
on,'' Karl said. ''They'll let anyone wear whatever they want up
there.''
</P>
<P>
   Bell was upset about the situation, but said it was not an
excuse.
</P>
<P>
   ''That's not what beat us,'' Bell said. ''We really didn't play
very well.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
